{
  "text": "Compound A was originally from a Japan Tobacco/Tularik collaboration from which it (T863) was further characterized as a tool compound by the Pfizer group [CITATION_1] . This compound contains an aminopyrimidine oxazine heterocyclic core appended to a phenylcyclohexane acetic acid pharmacophore. The carboxylic acid moiety has been a standard structure feature on most subsequent DGAT1 inhibitor designs, since it adds solubility and improves pharmacokinetics and potency [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29683588",
